Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Phase 1b of the production-readiness pass — closes the top type-safety
gap that survived Phase 1a's mechanical sweep, and unifies how the
codebase imports drizzle-orm query helpers.

== Root cause being fixed ==

pnpm's peer-dependency hashing was resolving `drizzle-orm` to multiple
distinct copies (one per peer subgraph). Routes that did
`import { eq, sql } from "drizzle-orm"` ended up with operator types
from a *different* drizzle-orm instance than the columns coming from
`@workspace/db`'s `pgTable(...)`. tsc then complained that
`AnyColumn`/`SQLWrapper` from "drizzle-orm A" didn't match "drizzle-orm
B" on every `.where(eq(table.col, val))` call.

== Fix ==

1. lib/db/src/index.ts — re-export every drizzle-orm operator we use
   (and, asc, between, count, countDistinct, desc, eq, exists, gt,
   gte, ilike, inArray, isNotNull, isNull, like, lt, lte, max, min,
   ne, not, notBetween, notExists, notIlike, notInArray, notLike, or,
   sql, sum). All consumers now import from a single drizzle-orm
   instance via @workspace/db.

2. ~50 routes + lib files — switched
     import { eq, desc, ... } from "drizzle-orm";
   to
     import { eq, desc, ... } from "@workspace/db";

3. Surgical TS fixes across ~70 files: `unknown` narrowing, explicit
   discriminator casts on Express handlers, pino logger object shape,
   numeric-string parsing helpers (lib/utils/params.ts: paramString,
   paramSymbol, paramInt, paramFloat, paramEnum), Zod schema generic
   inference, and the SubsystemStatus union widening in
   production_observability.

4. Test mocks — every `vi.mock("@workspace/db", ...)` block in
   __tests__/ was extended to re-export drizzle-orm operator stubs:
       and:       (...args) => args        // passthrough
       eq, ne, gt, gte, lt, lte, isNull,
       isNotNull, desc, asc, inArray,
       notInArray, between, like, ilike,
       exists, not                          // () => null
       count, sum, max, min                 // () => 0/null
       sql:  Object.assign(vi.fn(() => ""),
                          { raw: vi.fn((s) => s) })
   `sql` is wrapped in `Object.assign(callable, { raw })` because the
   route uses both `sql\`count(*)\`` (tagged template — needs callable)
   and `sql.raw(...)` (needs the .raw method).

== Verification ==

- npx tsc --build               → exit 0
- artifacts/api-server tsc      → exit 0
- artifacts/api-server vitest run:
    Test Files   1 failed | 178 passed (179)
    Tests       18 failed | 3654 passed (3672)

== Known pre-existing blocker (NOT a Phase 1b regression) ==

src/__tests__/execution_validator.test.ts (18 tests) fails to load the
better-sqlite3 native binding:
  Error: Could not locate the bindings file. Tried: …
         better_sqlite3.node not present in any expected build path.

Confirmed identical failure on the pre-Phase-1b baseline (git stash +
re-run). Root cause: the sandbox cannot reach
nodejs.org/download/release/v22.22.0/node-v22.22.0-headers.tar.gz to
build the native module from source, and the prebuilt binary for the
sandbox arch (linux/arm64, NODE_MODULE_VERSION 127) was not in the
better-sqlite3 prebuild manifest. This will resolve automatically on
any developer/CI machine with normal network egress (the postinstall
prebuild-install hook runs there). Tracked separately from Phase 1b.

== Out of scope (Phase 1c) ==

- Tail-70 surgical fixes
- Remove `continue-on-error: true` from .github/workflows/ci.yml line 39

